				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Mana regen<a name="10448"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 18 03 1:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>As a 65 bard (low-end average gear, non-raiding guild) I can fade twice on my mana pool.  Mana regen is a key issue if I'm pulling in tricky places or have just been rez'ed (main puller for guild 90% of the time).  I've also been swarm kiting in PoN with high 40's, low 50's guildees grouped to power level them some.  This drains mana pretty quickly.  Aside from a couple of bonuses from levels (think we get 1 extra mana per tick at 62 and 65) I have MC1 from the archtype AAs, and 2 FT1 items.  This is enough to serve in most cases.  
<br />

<br />
I always have my Soltice Earring equip'ed.  I recommend getting one of these as they tend to be fairly cheap (although I never have more than 2k, so it took me a bit to get).  The other item is a range item that I switch out when I need the extra mana.  This item is the result of the Hollowshade Moor war.  There is a good guide to it on The Concert Hall message boards.  You can look at TCH or email me and I'll do a summary of how to do it.
<br />

<br />
MC1, my two FT 1 items, and lvl based regen is enough to serve me in most situations.  There are some FT3 boots, the shawl quests, and others that can give huge boosts, but I have never felt the overwhelming need to get them.
<br />

<br />
/ramble off
<br />

<br />
